  nickname: heb
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 433894a244f646848a22a9c7d127b66b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus Christ Is God\u2019s Son"
      title: "Jesus Christ Is God\u2019s Son"
      number: 1
      content: '  Long ago God spoke many times and in many ways to our ancestors
        through the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And now in these final days, he has spoken to us through his Son.
        God promised everything to the Son as an inheritance, and through the Son
        he created the universe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The Son radiates God\u2019s own glory and expresses the very character
        of God, and he sustains everything by the mighty power of his command. When
        he had cleansed us from our sins, he sat down in the place of honor at the
        right hand of the majestic God in heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Son Is Greater Than the Angels'
      title: The Son Is Greater Than the Angels
      number: 4
      content: 'This shows that the Son is far greater than the angels, just as the
        name God gave him is greater than their names.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For God never said to any angel what he said to Jesus:\u201CYou are
        my Son.Today I have become your Father.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201DGod also said,\u201CI
        will be his Father,and he will be my Son.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:5a '
        content: Or <b>Today I reveal you as my Son. </b>Ps 2:7.
      - number: '1:5b '
        content: 2 Sam 7:14.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when he brought his supreme[[COMMENT(0)]] Son into the world,
        God said,[[COMMENT(1)]]\u201CLet all of God\u2019s angels worship him.\u201D[[COMMENT(2)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:6a '
        content: Or <b>firstborn.</b>
      - number: '1:6b '
        content: Or <b>when he again brings his supreme Son </b>[or <b>firstborn
          Son</b>] <b>into the world, God will say.</b>
      - number: '1:6c '
        content: Deut 32:43.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Regarding the angels, he says,\u201CHe sends his angels like the
        winds,his servants like flames of fire.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        content: Ps 104:4 (Greek version).
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But to the Son he says,\u201CYour throne, O God, endures forever
        and ever.You rule with a scepter of justice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You love justice and hate evil.Therefore, O God, your God has anointed
        you,pouring out the oil of joy on you more than on anyone else.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:8-9 '
        content: Ps 45:6-7.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He also says to the Son,\u201CIn the beginning, Lord, you laid the
        foundation of the earthand made the heavens with your hands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They will perish, but you remain forever.They will wear out like
        old clothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You will fold them up like a cloakand discard them like old clothing.But
        you are always the same;you will live forever.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:10-12 '
        content: Ps 102:25-27.
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And God never said to any of the angels,\u201CSit in the place of
        honor at my right handuntil I humble your enemies,making them a footstool
        under your feet.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:13 '
        content: Ps 110:1.
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore, angels are only servants\u2014spirits sent to care for
        people who will inherit salvation."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Warning against Drifting Away'
      title: A Warning against Drifting Away
      number: 1
      content: '  So we must listen very carefully to the truth we have heard, or
        we may drift away from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the message God delivered through angels has always stood firm,
        and every violation of the law and every act of disobedience was punished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So what makes us think we can escape if we ignore this great salvation
        that was first announced by the Lord Jesus himself and then delivered to
        us by those who heard him speak? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Jesus, the Man'
      title: Jesus, the Man
      number: 4
      content: 'And God confirmed the message by giving signs and wonders and various
        miracles and gifts of the Holy Spirit whenever he chose.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And furthermore, it is not angels who will control the future world
        we are talking about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For in one place the Scriptures say,\u201CWhat are mere mortals that
        you should think about them,or a son of man[[COMMENT(0)]] that you should
        care for him?  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:6 '
        content: Or <b>the Son of Man.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yet for a little while you made them a little lower than the angelsand
        crowned them with glory and honor.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:7 '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>You gave them charge of everything you made.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You gave them authority over all things.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]Now when
        it says \u201Call things,\u201D it means nothing is left out. But we have
        not yet seen all things put under their authority. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:6-8 '
        content: Ps 8:4-6 (Greek version).
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "What we do see is Jesus, who for a little while was given a position
        \u201Ca little lower than the angels\u201D; and because he suffered death
        for us, he is now \u201Ccrowned with glory and honor.\u201D Yes, by God\u2019s
        grace, Jesus tasted death for everyone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'God, for whom and through whom everything was made, chose to bring
        many children into glory. And it was only right that he should make Jesus,
        through his suffering, a perfect leader, fit to bring them into their salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So now Jesus and the ones he makes holy have the same Father. That
        is why Jesus is not ashamed to call them his brothers and sisters.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers; </b>also in 2:12.
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For he said to God,\u201CI will proclaim your name to my brothers
        and sisters.I will praise you among your assembled people.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:12 '
        content: Ps 22:22.
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He also said,\u201CI will put my trust in him,\u201Dthat is, \u201CI
        and the children God has given me.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:13 '
        content: Isa 8:17-18.
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Because God\u2019s children are human beings\u2014made of flesh and
        blood\u2014the Son also became flesh and blood. For only as a human being
        could he die, and only by dying could he break the power of the devil, who
        had[[COMMENT(0)]] the power of death. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:14 '
        content: Or <b>has.</b>
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Only in this way could he set free all who have lived their lives
        as slaves to the fear of dying.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'We also know that the Son did not come to help angels; he came to
        help the descendants of Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore, it was necessary for him to be made in every respect like
        us, his brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] so that he could be our merciful
        and faithful High Priest before God. Then he could offer a sacrifice that
        would take away the sins of the people. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:17 '
        content: Greek <b>like the brothers.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Since he himself has gone through suffering and testing, he is able
        to help us when we are being tested.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Is Greater Than Moses'
      title: Jesus Is Greater Than Moses
      number: 1
      content: "  And so, dear brothers and sisters who belong to God and[[COMMENT(0)]]
        are partners with those called to heaven, think carefully about this Jesus
        whom we declare to be God\u2019s messenger[[COMMENT(1)]] and High Priest. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1a '
        content: Greek <b>And so, holy brothers who.</b>
      - number: '3:1b '
        content: "Greek <b>God\u2019s apostle.</b>"
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For he was faithful to God, who appointed him, just as Moses served
        faithfully when he was entrusted with God\u2019s entire[[COMMENT(0)]] house.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>entire.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But Jesus deserves far more glory than Moses, just as a person who
        builds a house deserves more praise than the house itself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For every house has a builder, but the one who built everything is
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Moses was certainly faithful in God\u2019s house as a servant. His
        work was an illustration of the truths God would reveal later. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Christ, as the Son, is in charge of God\u2019s entire house.
        And we are God\u2019s house, if we keep our courage and remain confident
        in our hope in Christ.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>faithful to the end.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "That is why the Holy Spirit says,\u201CToday when you hear his voice,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "don\u2019t harden your heartsas Israel did when they rebelled,when
        they tested me in the wilderness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'There your ancestors tested and tried my patience,even though they
        saw my miracles for forty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So I was angry with them, and I said,\u2018Their hearts always turn
        away from me.They refuse to do what I tell them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So in my anger I took an oath:\u2018They will never enter my place
        of rest.\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:7-11 '
        content: Ps 95:7-11.
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Be careful then, dear brothers and sisters.[[COMMENT(0)]] Make sure
        that your own hearts are not evil and unbelieving, turning you away from
        the living God. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You must warn each other every day, while it is still \u201Ctoday,\u201D
        so that none of you will be deceived by sin and hardened against God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For if we are faithful to the end, trusting God just as firmly as
        when we first believed, we will share in all that belongs to Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Remember what it says:\u201CToday when you hear his voice,don\u2019t
        harden your heartsas Israel did when they rebelled.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:15 '
        content: Ps 95:7-8.
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And who was it who rebelled against God, even though they heard his
        voice? Wasn\u2019t it the people Moses led out of Egypt? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And who made God angry for forty years? Wasn\u2019t it the people
        who sinned, whose corpses lay in the wilderness? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And to whom was God speaking when he took an oath that they would
        never enter his rest? Wasn\u2019t it the people who disobeyed him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: So we see that because of their unbelief they were not able to enter
        his rest.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Promised Rest for God\u2019s People"
      title: "Promised Rest for God\u2019s People"
      number: 1
      content: "  God\u2019s promise of entering his rest still stands, so we ought
        to tremble with fear that some of you might fail to experience it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For this good news\u2014that God has prepared this rest\u2014has
        been announced to us just as it was to them. But it did them no good because
        they didn\u2019t share the faith of those who listened to God.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:2 '
        content: "Some manuscripts read <b>they didn\u2019t combine what they heard
          with faith.</b>"
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For only we who believe can enter his rest. As for the others, God
        said,\u201CIn my anger I took an oath:\u2018They will never enter my place
        of rest,\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]even though this rest has been ready since
        he made the world. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        content: Ps 95:11.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "We know it is ready because of the place in the Scriptures where
        it mentions the seventh day: \u201COn the seventh day God rested from all
        his work.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: Gen 2:2.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But in the other passage God said, \u201CThey will never enter my
        place of rest.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:5 '
        content: Ps 95:11.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So God\u2019s rest is there for people to enter, but those who first
        heard this good news failed to enter because they disobeyed God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So God set another time for entering his rest, and that time is today.
        God announced this through David much later in the words already quoted:\u201CToday
        when you hear his voice,don\u2019t harden your hearts.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: Ps 95:7-8.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now if Joshua had succeeded in giving them this rest, God would not
        have spoken about another day of rest still to come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So there is a special rest[[COMMENT(0)]] still waiting for the people
        of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:9 '
        content: Or <b>a Sabbath rest.</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For all who have entered into God\u2019s rest have rested from their
        labors, just as God did after creating the world. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So let us do our best to enter that rest. But if we disobey God,
        as the people of Israel did, we will fall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the word of God is alive and powerful. It is sharper than the
        sharpest two-edged sword, cutting between soul and spirit, between joint
        and marrow. It exposes our innermost thoughts and desires. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Christ Is Our High Priest'
      title: Christ Is Our High Priest
      number: 13
      content: 'Nothing in all creation is hidden from God. Everything is naked and
        exposed before his eyes, and he is the one to whom we are accountable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So then, since we have a great High Priest who has entered heaven,
        Jesus the Son of God, let us hold firmly to what we believe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'This High Priest of ours understands our weaknesses, for he faced
        all of the same testings we do, yet he did not sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So let us come boldly to the throne of our gracious God. There we
        will receive his mercy, and we will find grace to help us when we need it
        most.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Every high priest is a man chosen to represent other people in
        their dealings with God. He presents their gifts to God and offers sacrifices
        for their sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he is able to deal gently with ignorant and wayward people because
        he himself is subject to the same weaknesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'That is why he must offer sacrifices for his own sins as well as
        theirs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And no one can become a high priest simply because he wants such
        an honor. He must be called by God for this work, just as Aaron was. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "That is why Christ did not honor himself by assuming he could become
        High Priest. No, he was chosen by God, who said to him,\u201CYou are my Son.Today
        I have become your Father.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: Or <b>Today I reveal you as my Son. </b>Ps 2:7.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And in another passage God said to him,\u201CYou are a priest forever
        in the order of Melchizedek.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        content: Ps 110:4.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'While Jesus was here on earth, he offered prayers and pleadings,
        with a loud cry and tears, to the one who could rescue him from death. And
        God heard his prayers because of his deep reverence for God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Even though Jesus was God\u2019s Son, he learned obedience from the
        things he suffered. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In this way, God qualified him as a perfect High Priest, and he became
        the source of eternal salvation for all those who obey him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: A Call to Spiritual Growth'
      title: A Call to Spiritual Growth
      number: 10
      content: 'And God designated him to be a High Priest in the order of Melchizedek.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "There is much more we would like to say about this, but it is difficult
        to explain, especially since you are spiritually dull and don\u2019t seem
        to listen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You have been believers so long now that you ought to be teaching
        others. Instead, you need someone to teach you again the basic things about
        God\u2019s word.[[COMMENT(0)]] You are like babies who need milk and cannot
        eat solid food. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:12 '
        content: Or <b>about the oracles of God.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For someone who lives on milk is still an infant and doesn\u2019t
        know how to do what is right. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Solid food is for those who are mature, who through training have
        the skill to recognize the difference between right and wrong.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  So let us stop going over the basic teachings about Christ again
        and again. Let us go on instead and become mature in our understanding. Surely
        we don\u2019t need to start again with the fundamental importance of repenting
        from evil deeds[[COMMENT(0)]] and placing our faith in God. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: Greek <b>from dead works.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "You don\u2019t need further instruction about baptisms, the laying
        on of hands, the resurrection of the dead, and eternal judgment. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And so, God willing, we will move forward to further understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For it is impossible to bring back to repentance those who were once
        enlightened\u2014those who have experienced the good things of heaven and
        shared in the Holy Spirit, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "who have tasted the goodness of the word of God and the power of
        the age to come\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and who then turn away from God. It is impossible to bring such people
        back to repentance; by rejecting the Son of God, they themselves are nailing
        him to the cross once again and holding him up to public shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the ground soaks up the falling rain and bears a good crop for
        the farmer, it has God\u2019s blessing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But if a field bears thorns and thistles, it is useless. The farmer
        will soon condemn that field and burn it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Dear friends, even though we are talking this way, we really don\u2019t
        believe it applies to you. We are confident that you are meant for better
        things, things that come with salvation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For God is not unjust. He will not forget how hard you have worked
        for him and how you have shown your love to him by caring for other believers,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        as you still do. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:10 '
        content: "Greek <b>for God\u2019s holy people.</b>"
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Our great desire is that you will keep on loving others as long as
        life lasts, in order to make certain that what you hope for will come true. '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: God\u2019s Promises Bring Hope"
      title: "God\u2019s Promises Bring Hope"
      number: 12
      content: "Then you will not become spiritually dull and indifferent. Instead,
        you will follow the example of those who are going to inherit God\u2019s
        promises because of their faith and endurance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For example, there was God\u2019s promise to Abraham. Since there
        was no one greater to swear by, God took an oath in his own name, saying:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI will certainly bless you,and I will multiply your descendants
        beyond number.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:14 '
        content: Gen 22:17.
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Abraham waited patiently, and he received what God had promised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now when people take an oath, they call on someone greater than themselves
        to hold them to it. And without any question that oath is binding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'God also bound himself with an oath, so that those who received the
        promise could be perfectly sure that he would never change his mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So God has given both his promise and his oath. These two things
        are unchangeable because it is impossible for God to lie. Therefore, we who
        have fled to him for refuge can have great confidence as we hold to the hope
        that lies before us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "This hope is a strong and trustworthy anchor for our souls. It leads
        us through the curtain into God\u2019s inner sanctuary. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Jesus has already gone in there for us. He has become our eternal
        High Priest in the order of Melchizedek.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Melchizedek Is Greater Than Abraham'
      title: Melchizedek Is Greater Than Abraham
      number: 1
      content: '  This Melchizedek was king of the city of Salem and also a priest
        of God Most High. When Abraham was returning home after winning a great battle
        against the kings, Melchizedek met him and blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Abraham took a tenth of all he had captured in battle and gave
        it to Melchizedek. The name Melchizedek means \u201Cking of justice,\u201D
        and king of Salem means \u201Cking of peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "There is no record of his father or mother or any of his ancestors\u2014no
        beginning or end to his life. He remains a priest forever, resembling the
        Son of God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Consider then how great this Melchizedek was. Even Abraham, the great
        patriarch of Israel, recognized this by giving him a tenth of what he had
        taken in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the law of Moses required that the priests, who are descendants
        of Levi, must collect a tithe from the rest of the people of Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who are also descendants of Abraham. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:5 '
        content: Greek <b>from their brothers.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But Melchizedek, who was not a descendant of Levi, collected a tenth
        from Abraham. And Melchizedek placed a blessing upon Abraham, the one who
        had already received the promises of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And without question, the person who has the power to give a blessing
        is greater than the one who is blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The priests who collect tithes are men who die, so Melchizedek is
        greater than they are, because we are told that he lives on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "In addition, we might even say that these Levites\u2014the ones who
        collect the tithe\u2014paid a tithe to Melchizedek when their ancestor Abraham
        paid a tithe to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For although Levi wasn\u2019t born yet, the seed from which he came
        was in Abraham\u2019s body when Melchizedek collected the tithe from him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So if the priesthood of Levi, on which the law was based, could have
        achieved the perfection God intended, why did God need to establish a different
        priesthood, with a priest in the order of Melchizedek instead of the order
        of Levi and Aaron?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:11 '
        content: Greek <b>the order of Aaron?</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And if the priesthood is changed, the law must also be changed to
        permit it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the priest we are talking about belongs to a different tribe,
        whose members have never served at the altar as priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Jesus Is like Melchizedek'
      title: Jesus Is like Melchizedek
      number: 14
      content: 'What I mean is, our Lord came from the tribe of Judah, and Moses
        never mentioned priests coming from that tribe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'This change has been made very clear since a different priest, who
        is like Melchizedek, has appeared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Jesus became a priest, not by meeting the physical requirement of
        belonging to the tribe of Levi, but by the power of a life that cannot be
        destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the psalmist pointed this out when he prophesied,\u201CYou are
        a priest forever in the order of Melchizedek.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:17 '
        content: Ps 110:4.
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Yes, the old requirement about the priesthood was set aside because
        it was weak and useless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For the law never made anything perfect. But now we have confidence
        in a better hope, through which we draw near to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "This new system was established with a solemn oath. Aaron\u2019s
        descendants became priests without such an oath, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but there was an oath regarding Jesus. For God said to him,\u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has taken an oath and will not break his vow:\u2018You
        are a priest forever.\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:21 '
        content: Ps 110:4.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Because of this oath, Jesus is the one who guarantees this better
        covenant with God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'There were many priests under the old system, for death prevented
        them from remaining in office. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But because Jesus lives forever, his priesthood lasts forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Therefore he is able, once and forever, to save[[COMMENT(0)]] those
        who come to God through him. He lives forever to intercede with God on their
        behalf.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:25 '
        content: Or <b>is able to save completely.</b>
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He is the kind of high priest we need because he is holy and blameless,
        unstained by sin. He has been set apart from sinners and has been given the
        highest place of honor in heaven.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:26 '
        content: Or <b>has been exalted higher than the heavens.</b>
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Unlike those other high priests, he does not need to offer sacrifices
        every day. They did this for their own sins first and then for the sins of
        the people. But Jesus did this once for all when he offered himself as the
        sacrifice for the people\u2019s sins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: The law appointed high priests who were limited by human weakness.
        But after the law was given, God appointed his Son with an oath, and his
        Son has been made the perfect High Priest forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Christ Is Our High Priest'
      title: Christ Is Our High Priest
      number: 1
      content: '  Here is the main point: We have a High Priest who sat down in the
        place of honor beside the throne of the majestic God in heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There he ministers in the heavenly Tabernacle,[[COMMENT(0)]] the
        true place of worship that was built by the Lord and not by human hands.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:2 '
        content: Or <b>tent; </b>also in 8:5.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And since every high priest is required to offer gifts and sacrifices,
        our High Priest must make an offering, too. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If he were here on earth, he would not even be a priest, since there
        already are priests who offer the gifts required by the law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They serve in a system of worship that is only a copy, a shadow of
        the real one in heaven. For when Moses was getting ready to build the Tabernacle,
        God gave him this warning: \u201CBe sure that you make everything according
        to the pattern I have shown you here on the mountain.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:5 '
        content: Exod 25:40; 26:30.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But now Jesus, our High Priest, has been given a ministry that is
        far superior to the old priesthood, for he is the one who mediates for us
        a far better covenant with God, based on better promises.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If the first covenant had been faultless, there would have been no
        need for a second covenant to replace it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But when God found fault with the people, he said:\u201CThe day is
        coming, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,when I will make a new covenantwith
        the people of Israel and Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'This covenant will not be like the oneI made with their ancestorswhen
        I took them by the handand led them out of the land of Egypt.They did not
        remain faithful to my covenant,so I turned my back on them, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But this is the new covenant I will makewith the people of Israel
        on that day,[[COMMENT(0)]] says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:I will put
        my laws in their minds,and I will write them on their hearts.I will be their
        God,and they will be my people.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:10 '
        content: Greek <b>after those days.</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And they will not need to teach their neighbors,nor will they need
        to teach their relatives,[[COMMENT(0)]]saying, \u2018You should know the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019For everyone, from the least to the greatest,will
        know me already.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:11 '
        content: Greek <b>their brother.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And I will forgive their wickedness,and I will never again remember
        their sins.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:8-12 '
        content: Jer 31:31-34.
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When God speaks of a \u201Cnew\u201D covenant, it means he has made
        the first one obsolete. It is now out of date and will soon disappear."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Old Rules about Worship'
      title: Old Rules about Worship
      number: 1
      content: '  That first covenant between God and Israel had regulations for
        worship and a place of worship here on earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There were two rooms in that Tabernacle.[[COMMENT(0)]] In the first
        room were a lampstand, a table, and sacred loaves of bread on the table.
        This room was called the Holy Place. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:2 '
        content: Or <b>tent; </b>also in 9:11, 21.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then there was a curtain, and behind the curtain was the second room[[COMMENT(0)]]
        called the Most Holy Place. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:3 '
        content: Greek <b>second tent.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "In that room were a gold incense altar and a wooden chest called
        the Ark of the Covenant, which was covered with gold on all sides. Inside
        the Ark were a gold jar containing manna, Aaron\u2019s staff that sprouted
        leaves, and the stone tablets of the covenant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Above the Ark were the cherubim of divine glory, whose wings stretched
        out over the Ark\u2019s cover, the place of atonement. But we cannot explain
        these things in detail now.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When these things were all in place, the priests regularly entered
        the first room[[COMMENT(0)]] as they performed their religious duties. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:6 '
        content: Greek <b>first tent.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But only the high priest ever entered the Most Holy Place, and only
        once a year. And he always offered blood for his own sins and for the sins
        the people had committed in ignorance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'By these regulations the Holy Spirit revealed that the entrance to
        the Most Holy Place was not freely open as long as the Tabernacle[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and the system it represented were still in use.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:8 '
        content: Or <b>the first room; </b>Greek reads <b>the first tent.</b>
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'This is an illustration pointing to the present time. For the gifts
        and sacrifices that the priests offer are not able to cleanse the consciences
        of the people who bring them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Christ Is the Perfect Sacrifice'
      title: Christ Is the Perfect Sacrifice
      number: 10
      content: "For that old system deals only with food and drink and various cleansing
        ceremonies\u2014physical regulations that were in effect only until a better
        system could be established.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Christ has now become the High Priest over all the good things
        that have come.[[COMMENT(0)]] He has entered that greater, more perfect Tabernacle
        in heaven, which was not made by human hands and is not part of this created
        world. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:11 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>that are about to come.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "With his own blood\u2014not the blood of goats and calves\u2014he
        entered the Most Holy Place once for all time and secured our redemption
        forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Under the old system, the blood of goats and bulls and the ashes
        of a heifer could cleanse people\u2019s bodies from ceremonial impurity. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Just think how much more the blood of Christ will purify our consciences
        from sinful deeds[[COMMENT(0)]] so that we can worship the living God. For
        by the power of the eternal Spirit, Christ offered himself to God as a perfect
        sacrifice for our sins. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:14 '
        content: Greek <b>from dead works.</b>
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'That is why he is the one who mediates a new covenant between God
        and people, so that all who are called can receive the eternal inheritance
        God has promised them. For Christ died to set them free from the penalty
        of the sins they had committed under that first covenant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now when someone leaves a will,[[COMMENT(0)]] it is necessary to
        prove that the person who made it is dead.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:16a '
        content: Or <b>covenant; </b>also in 9:17.
      - number: '9:16b '
        content: Or <b>Now when someone makes a covenant, it is necessary to ratify
          it with the death of a sacrifice.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The will goes into effect only after the person\u2019s death. While
        the person who made it is still alive, the will cannot be put into effect.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'That is why even the first covenant was put into effect with the
        blood of an animal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For after Moses had read each of God\u2019s commandments to all the
        people, he took the blood of calves and goats,[[COMMENT(0)]] along with water,
        and sprinkled both the book of God\u2019s law and all the people, using hyssop
        branches and scarlet wool. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:19 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>and goats.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then he said, \u201CThis blood confirms the covenant God has made
        with you.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:20 '
        content: Exod 24:8.
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And in the same way, he sprinkled blood on the Tabernacle and on
        everything used for worship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In fact, according to the law of Moses, nearly everything was purified
        with blood. For without the shedding of blood, there is no forgiveness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'That is why the Tabernacle and everything in it, which were copies
        of things in heaven, had to be purified by the blood of animals. But the
        real things in heaven had to be purified with far better sacrifices than
        the blood of animals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For Christ did not enter into a holy place made with human hands,
        which was only a copy of the true one in heaven. He entered into heaven itself
        to appear now before God on our behalf. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And he did not enter heaven to offer himself again and again, like
        the high priest here on earth who enters the Most Holy Place year after year
        with the blood of an animal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'If that had been necessary, Christ would have had to die again and
        again, ever since the world began. But now, once for all time, he has appeared
        at the end of the age[[COMMENT(0)]] to remove sin by his own death as a sacrifice.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:26 '
        content: Greek <b>the ages.</b>
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And just as each person is destined to die once and after that comes
        judgment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: so also Christ was offered once for all time as a sacrifice to take
        away the sins of many people. He will come again, not to deal with our sins,
        but to bring salvation to all who are eagerly waiting for him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Christ\u2019s Sacrifice Once for All"
      title: "Christ\u2019s Sacrifice Once for All"
      number: 1
      content: '  The old system under the law of Moses was only a shadow, a dim
        preview of the good things to come, not the good things themselves. The sacrifices
        under that system were repeated again and again, year after year, but they
        were never able to provide perfect cleansing for those who came to worship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'If they could have provided perfect cleansing, the sacrifices would
        have stopped, for the worshipers would have been purified once for all time,
        and their feelings of guilt would have disappeared.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But instead, those sacrifices actually reminded them of their sins
        year after year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For it is not possible for the blood of bulls and goats to take away
        sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "That is why, when Christ[[COMMENT(0)]] came into the world, he said
        to God,\u201CYou did not want animal sacrifices or sin offerings.But you
        have given me a body to offer.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:5 '
        content: Greek <b>he; </b>also in 10:8.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You were not pleased with burnt offeringsor other offerings for sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then I said, \u2018Look, I have come to do your will, O God\u2014as
        is written about me in the Scriptures.\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:5-7 '
        content: Ps 40:6-8 (Greek version).
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "First, Christ said, \u201CYou did not want animal sacrifices or sin
        offerings or burnt offerings or other offerings for sin, nor were you pleased
        with them\u201D (though they are required by the law of Moses). "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then he said, \u201CLook, I have come to do your will.\u201D He cancels
        the first covenant in order to put the second into effect. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For God\u2019s will was for us to be made holy by the sacrifice of
        the body of Jesus Christ, once for all time.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Under the old covenant, the priest stands and ministers before the
        altar day after day, offering the same sacrifices again and again, which
        can never take away sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But our High Priest offered himself to God as a single sacrifice
        for sins, good for all time. Then he sat down in the place of honor at God\u2019s
        right hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'There he waits until his enemies are humbled and made a footstool
        under his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For by that one offering he forever made perfect those who are being
        made holy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Holy Spirit also testifies that this is so. For he says,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThis is the new covenant I will makewith my people on that
        day,[[COMMENT(0)]] says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:I will put my laws
        in their hearts,and I will write them on their minds.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:16a '
        content: Greek <b>after those days.</b>
      - number: '10:16b '
        content: Jer 31:33a.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he says,\u201CI will never again remembertheir sins and lawless
        deeds.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:17 '
        content: Jer 31:34b.
    - name: '18: A Call to Persevere'
      title: A Call to Persevere
      number: 18
      content: 'And when sins have been forgiven, there is no need to offer any more
        sacrifices.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And so, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] we can boldly enter
        heaven\u2019s Most Holy Place because of the blood of Jesus. "
      comments:
      - number: '10:19 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'By his death,[[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus opened a new and life-giving way
        through the curtain into the Most Holy Place. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:20 '
        content: Greek <b>Through his flesh.</b>
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And since we have a great High Priest who rules over God\u2019s house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "let us go right into the presence of God with sincere hearts fully
        trusting him. For our guilty consciences have been sprinkled with Christ\u2019s
        blood to make us clean, and our bodies have been washed with pure water.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Let us hold tightly without wavering to the hope we affirm, for God
        can be trusted to keep his promise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Let us think of ways to motivate one another to acts of love and
        good works. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And let us not neglect our meeting together, as some people do, but
        encourage one another, especially now that the day of his return is drawing
        near.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Dear friends, if we deliberately continue sinning after we have received
        knowledge of the truth, there is no longer any sacrifice that will cover
        these sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "There is only the terrible expectation of God\u2019s judgment and
        the raging fire that will consume his enemies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For anyone who refused to obey the law of Moses was put to death
        without mercy on the testimony of two or three witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Just think how much worse the punishment will be for those who have
        trampled on the Son of God, and have treated the blood of the covenant, which
        made us holy, as if it were common and unholy, and have insulted and disdained
        the Holy Spirit who brings God\u2019s mercy to us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For we know the one who said,\u201CI will take revenge.I will pay
        them back.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]He also said,\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will judge his own people.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:30a '
        content: Deut 32:35.
      - number: '10:30b '
        content: Deut 32:36.
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'It is a terrible thing to fall into the hands of the living God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Think back on those early days when you first learned about Christ.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Remember how you remained faithful even though it meant terrible suffering. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:32 '
        content: Greek <b>when you were first enlightened.</b>
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Sometimes you were exposed to public ridicule and were beaten, and
        sometimes you helped others who were suffering the same things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'You suffered along with those who were thrown into jail, and when
        all you owned was taken from you, you accepted it with joy. You knew there
        were better things waiting for you that will last forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So do not throw away this confident trust in the Lord. Remember the
        great reward it brings you! '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Patient endurance is what you need now, so that you will continue
        to do God\u2019s will. Then you will receive all that he has promised.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u201CFor in just a little while,the Coming One will come and not
        delay.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And my righteous ones will live by faith.[[COMMENT(0)]]But I will
        take no pleasure in anyone who turns away.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:38 '
        content: Or <b>my righteous ones will live by their faithfulness; </b>Greek
          reads <b>my righteous one will live by faith.</b>
      - number: '10:37-38 '
        content: Hab 2:3-4.
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: But we are not like those who turn away from God to their own destruction.
        We are the faithful ones, whose souls will be saved.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Great Examples of Faith'
      title: Great Examples of Faith
      number: 1
      content: '  Faith shows the reality of what we hope for; it is the evidence
        of things we cannot see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Through their faith, the people in days of old earned a good reputation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "By faith we understand that the entire universe was formed at God\u2019s
        command, that what we now see did not come from anything that can be seen.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It was by faith that Abel brought a more acceptable offering to God
        than Cain did. Abel\u2019s offering gave evidence that he was a righteous
        man, and God showed his approval of his gifts. Although Abel is long dead,
        he still speaks to us by his example of faith.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It was by faith that Enoch was taken up to heaven without dying\u2014\u201Che
        disappeared, because God took him.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] For before he was
        taken up, he was known as a person who pleased God. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:5 '
        content: Gen 5:24.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And it is impossible to please God without faith. Anyone who wants
        to come to him must believe that God exists and that he rewards those who
        sincerely seek him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It was by faith that Noah built a large boat to save his family from
        the flood. He obeyed God, who warned him about things that had never happened
        before. By his faith Noah condemned the rest of the world, and he received
        the righteousness that comes by faith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It was by faith that Abraham obeyed when God called him to leave
        home and go to another land that God would give him as his inheritance. He
        went without knowing where he was going. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And even when he reached the land God promised him, he lived there
        by faith\u2014for he was like a foreigner, living in tents. And so did Isaac
        and Jacob, who inherited the same promise. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Abraham was confidently looking forward to a city with eternal foundations,
        a city designed and built by God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'It was by faith that even Sarah was able to have a child, though
        she was barren and was too old. She believed[[COMMENT(0)]] that God would
        keep his promise. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:11 '
        content: Or <b>It was by faith that he [Abraham] was able to have a child,
          even though Sarah was barren and he was too old. He believed.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And so a whole nation came from this one man who was as good as dead\u2014a
        nation with so many people that, like the stars in the sky and the sand on
        the seashore, there is no way to count them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'All these people died still believing what God had promised them.
        They did not receive what was promised, but they saw it all from a distance
        and welcomed it. They agreed that they were foreigners and nomads here on
        earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Obviously people who say such things are looking forward to a country
        they can call their own. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If they had longed for the country they came from, they could have
        gone back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But they were looking for a better place, a heavenly homeland. That
        is why God is not ashamed to be called their God, for he has prepared a city
        for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "It was by faith that Abraham offered Isaac as a sacrifice when God
        was testing him. Abraham, who had received God\u2019s promises, was ready
        to sacrifice his only son, Isaac, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "even though God had told him, \u201CIsaac is the son through whom
        your descendants will be counted.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:18 '
        content: Gen 21:12.
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Abraham reasoned that if Isaac died, God was able to bring him back
        to life again. And in a sense, Abraham did receive his son back from the
        dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'It was by faith that Isaac promised blessings for the future to his
        sons, Jacob and Esau.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "It was by faith that Jacob, when he was old and dying, blessed each
        of Joseph\u2019s sons and bowed in worship as he leaned on his staff.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It was by faith that Joseph, when he was about to die, said confidently
        that the people of Israel would leave Egypt. He even commanded them to take
        his bones with them when they left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "It was by faith that Moses\u2019 parents hid him for three months
        when he was born. They saw that God had given them an unusual child, and
        they were not afraid to disobey the king\u2019s command.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "It was by faith that Moses, when he grew up, refused to be called
        the son of Pharaoh\u2019s daughter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He chose to share the oppression of God\u2019s people instead of
        enjoying the fleeting pleasures of sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He thought it was better to suffer for the sake of Christ than to
        own the treasures of Egypt, for he was looking ahead to his great reward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "It was by faith that Moses left the land of Egypt, not fearing the
        king\u2019s anger. He kept right on going because he kept his eyes on the
        one who is invisible. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'It was by faith that Moses commanded the people of Israel to keep
        the Passover and to sprinkle blood on the doorposts so that the angel of
        death would not kill their firstborn sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'It was by faith that the people of Israel went right through the
        Red Sea as though they were on dry ground. But when the Egyptians tried to
        follow, they were all drowned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'It was by faith that the people of Israel marched around Jericho
        for seven days, and the walls came crashing down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'It was by faith that Rahab the prostitute was not destroyed with
        the people in her city who refused to obey God. For she had given a friendly
        welcome to the spies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'How much more do I need to say? It would take too long to recount
        the stories of the faith of Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jephthah, David, Samuel,
        and all the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'By faith these people overthrew kingdoms, ruled with justice, and
        received what God had promised them. They shut the mouths of lions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'quenched the flames of fire, and escaped death by the edge of the
        sword. Their weakness was turned to strength. They became strong in battle
        and put whole armies to flight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Women received their loved ones back again from death.But others
        were tortured, refusing to turn from God in order to be set free. They placed
        their hope in a better life after the resurrection. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Some were jeered at, and their backs were cut open with whips. Others
        were chained in prisons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Some died by stoning, some were sawed in half,[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        others were killed with the sword. Some went about wearing skins of sheep
        and goats, destitute and oppressed and mistreated. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:37 '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>some were tested.</b>
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'They were too good for this world, wandering over deserts and mountains,
        hiding in caves and holes in the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'All these people earned a good reputation because of their faith,
        yet none of them received all that God had promised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: For God had something better in mind for us, so that they would not
        reach perfection without us.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Discipline Proves His Love"
      title: "God\u2019s Discipline Proves His Love"
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore, since we are surrounded by such a huge crowd of witnesses
        to the life of faith, let us strip off every weight that slows us down, especially
        the sin that so easily trips us up. And let us run with endurance the race
        God has set before us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "We do this by keeping our eyes on Jesus, the champion who initiates
        and perfects our faith.[[COMMENT(0)]] Because of the joy[[COMMENT(1)]] awaiting
        him, he endured the cross, disregarding its shame. Now he is seated in the
        place of honor beside God\u2019s throne. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:2a '
        content: Or <b>Jesus, the originator and perfecter of our faith.</b>
      - number: '12:2b '
        content: Or <b>Instead of the joy.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Think of all the hostility he endured from sinful people;[[COMMENT(0)]]
        then you won\u2019t become weary and give up. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:3 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>Think of how people hurt themselves by
          opposing him.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After all, you have not yet given your lives in your struggle against
        sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And have you forgotten the encouraging words God spoke to you as
        his children?[[COMMENT(0)]] He said,\u201CMy child,[[COMMENT(1)]] don\u2019t
        make light of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s discipline,and don\u2019t
        give up when he corrects you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:5a '
        content: Greek <b>sons; </b>also in 12:7, 8.
      - number: '12:5b '
        content: Greek <b>son; </b>also in 12:6, 7.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> disciplines those he loves,and
        he punishes each one he accepts as his child.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:5-6 '
        content: Prov 3:11-12 (Greek version).
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'As you endure this divine discipline, remember that God is treating
        you as his own children. Who ever heard of a child who is never disciplined
        by its father? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If God doesn\u2019t discipline you as he does all of his children,
        it means that you are illegitimate and are not really his children at all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Since we respected our earthly fathers who disciplined us, shouldn\u2019t
        we submit even more to the discipline of the Father of our spirits, and live
        forever?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:9 '
        content: Or <b>and really live?</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For our earthly fathers disciplined us for a few years, doing the
        best they knew how. But God\u2019s discipline is always good for us, so that
        we might share in his holiness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "No discipline is enjoyable while it is happening\u2014it\u2019s painful!
        But afterward there will be a peaceful harvest of right living for those
        who are trained in this way.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So take a new grip with your tired hands and strengthen your weak
        knees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: A Call to Listen to God'
      title: A Call to Listen to God
      number: 13
      content: 'Mark out a straight path for your feet so that those who are weak
        and lame will not fall but become strong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Work at living in peace with everyone, and work at living a holy
        life, for those who are not holy will not see the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Look after each other so that none of you fails to receive the grace
        of God. Watch out that no poisonous root of bitterness grows up to trouble
        you, corrupting many. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Make sure that no one is immoral or godless like Esau, who traded
        his birthright as the firstborn son for a single meal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "You know that afterward, when he wanted his father\u2019s blessing,
        he was rejected. It was too late for repentance, even though he begged with
        bitter tears.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You have not come to a physical mountain,[[COMMENT(0)]] to a place
        of flaming fire, darkness, gloom, and whirlwind, as the Israelites did at
        Mount Sinai. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:18 '
        content: Greek <b>to something that can be touched.</b>
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For they heard an awesome trumpet blast and a voice so terrible that
        they begged God to stop speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "They staggered back under God\u2019s command: \u201CIf even an animal
        touches the mountain, it must be stoned to death.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:20 '
        content: Exod 19:13.
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Moses himself was so frightened at the sight that he said, \u201CI
        am terrified and trembling.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:21 '
        content: Deut 9:19.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'No, you have come to Mount Zion, to the city of the living God, the
        heavenly Jerusalem, and to countless thousands of angels in a joyful gathering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "You have come to the assembly of God\u2019s firstborn children, whose
        names are written in heaven. You have come to God himself, who is the judge
        over all things. You have come to the spirits of the righteous ones in heaven
        who have now been made perfect. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You have come to Jesus, the one who mediates the new covenant between
        God and people, and to the sprinkled blood, which speaks of forgiveness instead
        of crying out for vengeance like the blood of Abel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Be careful that you do not refuse to listen to the One who is speaking.
        For if the people of Israel did not escape when they refused to listen to
        Moses, the earthly messenger, we will certainly not escape if we reject the
        One who speaks to us from heaven! '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When God spoke from Mount Sinai his voice shook the earth, but now
        he makes another promise: \u201COnce again I will shake not only the earth
        but the heavens also.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:26 '
        content: Hag 2:6.
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'This means that all of creation will be shaken and removed, so that
        only unshakable things will remain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Since we are receiving a Kingdom that is unshakable, let us be thankful
        and please God by worshiping him with holy fear and awe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: For our God is a devouring fire.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Concluding Words'
      title: Concluding Words
      number: 1
      content: '  Keep on loving each other as brothers and sisters.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:1 '
        content: Greek <b>Continue in brotherly love.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Don\u2019t forget to show hospitality to strangers, for some who
        have done this have entertained angels without realizing it! "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Remember those in prison, as if you were there yourself. Remember
        also those being mistreated, as if you felt their pain in your own bodies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Give honor to marriage, and remain faithful to one another in marriage.
        God will surely judge people who are immoral and those who commit adultery.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Don\u2019t love money; be satisfied with what you have. For God has
        said,\u201CI will never fail you.I will never abandon you.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:5 '
        content: Deut 31:6, 8.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So we can say with confidence,\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is my helper,so I will have no fear.What can mere people do to me?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        content: Ps 118:6.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember your leaders who taught you the word of God. Think of all
        the good that has come from their lives, and follow the example of their
        faith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today, and forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So do not be attracted by strange, new ideas. Your strength comes
        from God\u2019s grace, not from rules about food, which don\u2019t help those
        who follow them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'We have an altar from which the priests in the Tabernacle[[COMMENT(0)]]
        have no right to eat. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:10 '
        content: Or <b>tent.</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Under the old system, the high priest brought the blood of animals
        into the Holy Place as a sacrifice for sin, and the bodies of the animals
        were burned outside the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So also Jesus suffered and died outside the city gates to make his
        people holy by means of his own blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So let us go out to him, outside the camp, and bear the disgrace
        he bore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For this world is not our permanent home; we are looking forward
        to a home yet to come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore, let us offer through Jesus a continual sacrifice of praise
        to God, proclaiming our allegiance to his name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And don\u2019t forget to do good and to share with those in need.
        These are the sacrifices that please God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Obey your spiritual leaders, and do what they say. Their work is
        to watch over your souls, and they are accountable to God. Give them reason
        to do this with joy and not with sorrow. That would certainly not be for
        your benefit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Pray for us, for our conscience is clear and we want to live honorably
        in everything we do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And especially pray that I will be able to come back to you soon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now may the God of peace\u2014who brought up from the dead our Lord
        Jesus,the great Shepherd of the sheep,and ratified an eternal covenant with
        his blood\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'may he equip you with all you needfor doing his will.May he produce
        in you,[[COMMENT(0)]]through the power of Jesus Christ,every good thing that
        is pleasing to him.All glory to him forever and ever! Amen.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:21 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>in us.</b>
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I urge you, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] to pay attention
        to what I have written in this brief exhortation.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:22 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I want you to know that our brother Timothy has been released from
        jail. If he comes here soon, I will bring him with me to see you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Greet all your leaders and all the believers there.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        The believers from Italy send you their greetings.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:24 '
        content: "Greek <b>all of God\u2019s holy people.</b>"
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "May God\u2019s grace be with you all."
      comments: []
